  "title": "Risk Management Associate/Assistant Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Risk Management</strong></p><ul><li>Monitor and report risk limit, risk indicators/measures</li><li>Conduct risk assessment to identify potential risks and vulnerabilities across the organization</li><li>Prepare risk management reports to senior management and stakeholders</li><li>Prepare Risk Management Committee material</li><li>Oversee Risk & Control Self-Assessment (RCSA) and incident management.</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure compliance with regulatory requirement and internal</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to ensure compliance with regulatory requirement and internal</li></ul><p><strong>Policies</strong></p><ul><li>Facilitate Risk projects/initiatives (e.g. Environmental Risk, Technology Risk, Outsourcing/Third Party Risk)</li><li>Assist with procedure management and other administrative support as needed</li><li>Participate in internal audits and inspections</li></ul><p><strong>Technology Risk Management (TRM) / IT:</strong></p><ul><li>Collaborate with IT and Security teams to ensure effective implementation of technology risk management strategies and initiatives // to ensure compliance with regulatory requirement and internal policies</li><li>Provide training on risk awareness and best practices</li></ul><p><strong>Requirement</strong></p><ul><li>Knowledge and understanding of derivatives, securities, and related products</li><li>Deep understanding of Capital markets and risk management regulations (Basel Ⅲ)</li><li>Holders of financial certifications such as CFA and FRM. etc</li><li>Must be proficient in Korean to effectively liaise with Korean counterparts and clients, ensuring smooth communication and understanding of business needs</li><li>Fresh graduates are welcome</li></ul>",
